{"name":"Read Magic","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>The ability to decipher otherwise unintelligible magical inscriptions or symbols placed on weapons, armour, items, doors, walls, and other media by means of the <em>sorcerer's mark</em> spell or other like methods.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"warlock","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251200032,"modifiedTime":1681579210131,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"ByAj6dcKEbw5NMD4","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Use","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 59\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To decipher and invoke scroll scrolls with spells that are included in the warlock&rsquo;s chosen school of sorcery: magician, cryomancer, necromancer, or pyromancer (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 93</strong>, <strong>94</strong>, <strong>96</strong>, or <strong>97</strong>), unless the scroll was created by an ecclesiastical sorcerer (one who casts cleric or druid spells).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"warlock","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251242630,"modifiedTime":1681579210132,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"IMMwhPSaQCOAlFnm","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Sorcery","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 59\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Warlocks cast spells that they memorize from arcane tomes. At character creation, the player must select which school of magic his or her warlock practices: that of the magician, cryomancer, necromancer, or pyromancer. This decision is irrevocable. The number and levels of spells cast per day are charted on <strong>Table 30</strong>, though warlocks of high intelligence gain bonus spells cast per day (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>intelligence</em>). For example, a 4th-level warlock with 13 intelligence can cast two level 1 spells and one level 2 spell per day.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 59\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>A warlock begins with a spell book that contains one level 1 spell selected from the <strong>Magician-</strong>, <strong>Cryomancer-</strong>, <strong>Necromancer-</strong>, or <strong>Pyromancer Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7</strong>, <strong>Table 93</strong>, <strong>94</strong>, <strong>96</strong>, or <strong>97</strong>), depending on which school of sorcery was selected at character creation. Through personal research, the warlock develops one new spell at each level gain; each is learnt automatically, with no need of a qualification roll, but it must be of a castable level (see <strong>Table 30</strong>).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial no. of spells known: &times;1</li>\n<li>No. of spells gained per level: &times;1</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Additional spells may be learnt outside of level training, but the process is more arduous (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <em>acquiring new spells</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"warlock","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251346735,"modifiedTime":1681579210132,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"MhpDOrvmcdZkPuv3","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Writing","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To scribe a known spell onto a scroll, creating a single-use magical device at a cost of 500 gp + 100 gp per spell level. Materials may include the finest vellum, paper, or papyrus; a fresh quill; and sorcerer&rsquo;s ink, such as sepia. This involved process requires one week per spell level.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"warlock","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251303706,"modifiedTime":1681579210132,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"Oifk1uU7408LhcAE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
